This year is team 6662’s first year doing swerve, but they only have 4 modules. So I designed a 3d-printed stand-in for them with swivel casters. That way, the team can build their robot using the models, and switch the actual modules off the practice bot once the main bot is finished. I think I a saw a similar design on CD previously, but I don’t think there was CAD. Maybe other teams will find this useful. Feel free to share similar models.

Here is the model (released under CC0):

Swerve crazy wheel Technical
I built our team a crazy wheel that fits the SDS MK4 modules. The idea is that when you fail -something- on your swerve module and need it working in a big hurry, you pull off the wheel and substitute this thing! Its a 4" Omni wheel with bearings in it, so it rolls any way you want, irrespective of what the swerve module is doing (steer OR drive)! I recently made some updates so that it uses the stock SDS bearings… Bore or drill out the hole in the AM-2948A Omni-wheel to anything over 1/2". …

And my latest version:
